title: [SOLVED]820-3115 macbook Pro 2012 - no backlight. F9700 fuse
message:
i've fixed many macbook's backlight in the past. but i dont recall pin 2 of F9700 still has power after i removed a dead F9700 fuse?

board is not liquid damage. 

it just has no backlight.

after i removed a dead F9700 fuse. i still get 0.6v power on pin2.  
i get a nice 12.6v on Pin 1 which is normal.


any advice. cheers :)

title: [SOLVED]820-3115 macbook Pro 2012 - no backlight. F9700 fuse
message: .6v is nothing. Caps on that side of the rail, disregard that voltage as it's essentially zero. Just replace fuse and move along diagnosing.

title: [SOLVED]820-3115 macbook Pro 2012 - no backlight. F9700 fuse
message: Thank you SMMRepair. The board is fixed. backlight has turned on and no flickering. :)
